premise_source_doc_sentence: Max B. Yasgur  (  December 15 , 1919 -- February 9 , 1973  )  was an American farmer , best known as the owner of the dairy farm in Bethel , New York , at which the Woodstock Music and Art Fair was held between August 15 and August 18 , 1969 .

Samuel S. `` Sam '' Yasgur  (  born 9 January 1942 - 23 June 2016  )  was an attorney ; Sullivan County , New York official ; and the son of Max Yasgur , who leased land on his 600 acre dairy farm in Bethel , New York for the Woodstock Music & Art Festival in August 1969 .

The Bethel Woods Center for the Arts is a not-for-profit performing arts center and museum located at the site of the 1969 Woodstock festival in Bethel , New York , which took place on a parcel of the original Max Yasgur 's Dairy Farm .
Since the space was too small , the producers then staged the festival on the farm of Max Yasgur about three miles northwest of White Lake .
The news broke even as Max Yasgur and the promoters were in a White Lake restaurant negotiating the details of the site .
